WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Other than that, I mean, it's been a ton of communicating.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:17.000
And, and most of what we're communicating is not really data science. It's more the value, the value proposition of what we're doing and why we're doing it.

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:37.000
Very, we always have one slide on like our, our technology stack that encompasses, you know, rstudio, AWS, Snowflake, data, data vendors, that's all kind of put on one, one slide of like a 10 slide deck.

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:51.000
So, other than that, we're always just talking about the value we're bringing, how it's going to help non data scientists, that's like a huge theme at the bank, you know, it's always about, it's always about lifting up teammates.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:58.000
You know, so if data science can help enhance other people's work, that's always like something people are very, very supportive of.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
Upskilling too.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:11.000
You know, a lot of people are interested in that but, but it's a lot of work to help upskill people but if, if you can find people who are willing to take on that work.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:17.000
I think it's, that's a big win also but that's really a lot of work. It's very time consuming.

00:01:18.000 --> 00:01:21.000
Especially, I mean at a big organization.

00:01:21.000 --> 00:01:32.000
That's been like a nine month project, just kind of getting on the training calendar of okay we want to start upskilling people on data science, teaching people about R etc.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:50.000
You know, creating the content and doing it that's like the easy part, getting it, getting it on the docket has been the hard part but, but I definitely think that trying to position data science as something that helps other people has been really important

00:01:51.000 --> 00:02:04.000
just because, again, there's, there's some hesitancy about data science there's some hesitancy about this new thing this new technology that could kind of take over what other people are doing so.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:10.000
Yeah, I think that that's been helpful too.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:25.000
So that was a positioning data science is something that helps other people and finding other like other little pockets of data science champions has has been has been a good way for us to approach things and help us figure out who we need to talk to about

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:26.000
different initiatives.

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:41.000
Thank you.

